text: Hello. I think i have the same problem. I can not enroll admin. All tests return with "Failed to initialize registrar".

<@U1Y2R5C9L> So query gives me info only from one peer? Also, when I added 4th peer, query on every peer gives me right info from all peers, not only one, but, when I invoked info on first validating peer and created additional peers after this, I didn't get info on first peer from additional peers. Invoking method saving info on ledger.
New fabric version comes without membersrv stuff. Can I use "facbrik-sdk-java"  without membersrv services?
<@U2SE05657>  not sure if I understand your issue, it is more like <#C0Y4PEU22|fabric>  stuff rather than sdk. Perhaps <@U13TWBRBL> or <@U0KN2SSKE> could help you with that
<@U2RSG61V2> the current sdk does not support fabric v1, you can use it with v0.6 though. Work for v1 is underway
<@U2SE05657>: yes query is executed only on the peer you invoked it on. But you can query from multiple peers if you want additional assurance
<@U2RSG61V2>: v1.0 fabric project doesn't have the member service because it's been moved to its own repo fabric-cop. It's also a brand new impl that'll require a new client for enrollment etc
